com.wordpress.loeper.kvv.base.exception

Class AmbiguousTargetException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.wordpress.loeper.kvv.base.exception.AmbiguousTargetException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NoTargetFoundException

    public class AmbiguousTargetException
extends java.lang.Exception
    Indicates that the previous request lacks information or was ambiguous. This exception is usually thrown if the KVV could not properly select origin and destination station. The most causes are similar station names. Sometimes if a user does a typo and no station could be found, the subclass NoTargetFoundException is thrown.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Martin Löper
